---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Alap — Astro Integration">
  <h1>Alap — Astro Integration</h1>
  <p>
    This example uses a local Astro integration to auto-inject Alap's web component
    and config into every page. No <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tags, no imports —
    just use <code>&lt;alap-link&gt;</code> anywhere.
  </p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><code>integrations/alap.mjs</code> defines a 15-line Astro integration</li>
    <li><code>astro.config.mjs</code> registers it with a path to the config file</li>
    <li>Every page gets <code>defineAlapLink()</code> and <code>registerConfig()</code> injected automatically</li>
    <li>Pages just use <code>&lt;alap-link query="..."&gt;</code> — zero boilerplate</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Try it</h2>
  <p>
    Browse <alap-link query=".coffee">coffee spots</alap-link>,
    check out <alap-link query="@favorites" id="favorites">my favorites</alap-link>,
    or explore <alap-link query=".nyc | .sf">both cities</alap-link>.
  </p>

  <h2>Why an integration?</h2>
  <p class="note">
    You <em>can</em> use the web component directly with a manual
    <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> block — that works fine for single pages.
    This integration approach scales better — add Alap links to any page without
    repeating setup code.
  </p>
</Base>
